Plot
Based on the true life experiences of poet Jimmy Santiago Baca, 
the film focuses on half-brothers Paco and Cruz, and their 
bi-racial cousin Miklo. It opens in 1972, as the three are 
members of an East L.A. gang known as the "Vatos Locos", and the 
story focuses on how a violent crime and the influence of 
narcotics alter their lives. Miklo is incarcerated and sent to 
San Quentin, where he makes a "home" for himself. Cruz becomes 
an exceptional artist, but a heroin addiction overcomes him with 
tragic results. Paco becomes a cop and an 
enemy to his "carnal", Miklo.
